Dr. Jill Biden delivered a speech at SXSWedu 2015, expressing her support for community colleges and the importance of education. She shared her experiences teaching at a community college and highlighted the diverse group of students she encounters, including single parents, veterans, and workers seeking advancement in their careers. Dr. Biden emphasized that the responsibility for educating students belongs to everyone and called for adapting to meet students' needs in order to increase graduation rates. She mentioned the work being done by community colleges, such as using innovative strategies and technology to improve student success. Dr. Biden also mentioned the Obama administration's efforts to invest in education, increase financial aid, and lower the cost of community college. She encouraged attendees to continue working towards accessible, affordable, and attainable education for all Americans.